"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-sport-athletics-2024-0822-1466233-one-irishman-and-the-strangest-race-in-olympic-history\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9 Sport journalist On this day 120 years ago, Great Britain added a silver medal to their Olympic haul - but that came via Galway man John Daly who finished second in the steeplechase event.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 49, \"end\": 62, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999066988739078, \"rank\": 9.329121409150925e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Galway\", \"score\": 0.7435434393092034, \"rank\": 0.2527918542857797, \"text\": \"Galway\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Galway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Galway\"}, {\"begin\": 137, \"end\": 146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Charles_Daly\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.3271543085209034e-21, \"text\": \"John Daly\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Charles_Daly\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Charles_Daly\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"RT\\u00c9 Sport journalist\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 20}, {\"ngram\": \"this day\", \"from\": 24, \"to\": 32}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver medal\", \"from\": 68, \"to\": 82}, {\"ngram\": \"their Olympic haul\", \"from\": 86, \"to\": 104}, {\"ngram\": \"the steeplechase event\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 191}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With Irish entries not appearing until the 1924 Olympics in Paris, Daly's silver in St Louis - and the gold medal claimed by Tipperary's Tom Kiely for all-around athletics - is part of Team GB's tally given there was no possibility of operating under the Ireland banner at the time.\", \"from\": 195, \"to\": 477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 200, \"end\": 205, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.7269795436886114, \"rank\": 0.37529272064333313, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999999958618, \"rank\": 4.145526674757997e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 279, \"end\": 287, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St._Louis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.399618574207288e-15, \"text\": \"St Louis\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St._Louis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/St._Louis\"}, {\"begin\": 320, \"end\": 329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tipperary_GAA\", \"score\": 0.991703526333277, \"rank\": 0.008365880972340417, \"text\": \"Tipperary\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tipperary_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tipperary_GAA\"}, {\"begin\": 332, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Kiely\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Kiely\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Kiely\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Kiely\"}, {\"begin\": 380, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.732912335631801, \"rank\": 0.3639790243332441, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 450, \"end\": 457, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999512869158874, \"rank\": 4.8715457027459535e-05, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 1924 Olympics\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 251}, {\"ngram\": \"Daly's silver\", \"from\": 262, \"to\": 275}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold medal\", \"from\": 294, \"to\": 308}, {\"ngram\": \"all-around athletics\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 366}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 372, \"to\": 376}, {\"ngram\": \"no possibility\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 426}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 468, \"to\": 476}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"John J Daly made his debut in the arena of American athletics and, undoubtedly, his maiden essay was one worthy of himself and his country,\\\" reported the Tuam Herald on 3 September 1904.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 523, \"end\": 531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999991889594787, \"rank\": 8.043964716831497e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 634, \"end\": 638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.156987933861857e-17, \"text\": \"Tuam\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John J Daly\", \"from\": 480, \"to\": 491}, {\"ngram\": \"his debut\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 506}, {\"ngram\": \"the arena\", \"from\": 510, \"to\": 519}, {\"ngram\": \"his maiden essay\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"his country\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 618}, {\"ngram\": \"3 September\", \"from\": 649, \"to\": 660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While gold trumps silver, and any medal is noteworthy, it was Daly rather than Kiely who has links to one of the most infamous events in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 821, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 692}, {\"ngram\": \"any medal\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"links\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 766}, {\"ngram\": \"the most infamous events\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 801}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 805, \"to\": 820}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John J, as he was often known, was a listed entry in the 1904 Olympic marathon in Missouri - a race simply absurd from start to finish.\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 905, \"end\": 913, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_Tigers\", \"score\": 0.9963771670512117, \"rank\": 0.0027049876419749613, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_Tigers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_Tigers\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"John J\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 829}, {\"ngram\": \"a listed entry\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 872}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1904 Olympic marathon\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 916, \"to\": 922}, {\"ngram\": \"start\", \"from\": 942, \"to\": 947}, {\"ngram\": \"finish\", \"from\": 951, \"to\": 957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eight of the 40 athletes, Daly included, opted not to partake.\", \"from\": 960, \"to\": 1022, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 40 athletes\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"Daly\", \"from\": 986, \"to\": 990}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With the event due to take place a day after his steeplechase success, it would be fair to assume that the conditions facing the athletes may have contributed to his U-turn, however, it seems that illness - including the sea sickness he suffered en-route to America - was mostly responsible.\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1314, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1037}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1050, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"his steeplechase success\", \"from\": 1068, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"the conditions\", \"from\": 1126, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1160}, {\"ngram\": \"his U\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1190}, {\"ngram\": \"turn\", \"from\": 1191, \"to\": 1195}, {\"ngram\": \"illness\", \"from\": 1220, \"to\": 1227}, {\"ngram\": \"the sea sickness\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1256}, {\"ngram\": \"en\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1271}, {\"ngram\": \"route\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I felt indisposed the day the marathon race was held,\\\" he said in a self-penned article in the Tuam Herald in December 1904.\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1441, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1412, \"end\": 1416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.156987933861857e-17, \"text\": \"Tuam\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tuam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the marathon race\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"a self-penned article\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1404}, {\"ngram\": \"December\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1435}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official Games website describes the marathon as \\\"the strangest race in Olympic history\\\" and if you think that is hyperbole, read on.\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1580, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The official Games website\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1469}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"the strangest race\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1515}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic history\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1534}, {\"ngram\": \"hyperbole\", \"from\": 1561, \"to\": 1570}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One runner, Cuba's Andar\\u00edn Carvajal, came to the start line in long trousers, a white shirt and walking shoes - an indication that not all were aware of what lay in store.\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1753, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"score\": 0.9999994690657832, \"rank\": 5.296887872363834e-07, \"text\": \"Cuba\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cuba\"}, {\"begin\": 1601, \"end\": 1617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andar\\u00edn_Carvajal\", \"score\": 0.999999999947704, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andar\\u00edn Carvajal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andar\\u00edn_Carvajal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andar\\u00edn_Carvajal\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One runner\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1592}, {\"ngram\": \"the start line\", \"from\": 1627, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"long trousers\", \"from\": 1645, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"an indication\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1707}, {\"ngram\": \"store\", \"from\": 1747, \"to\": 1752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carvajal would have a dramatic day with the sweltering heat and dusty course causing mayhem across the Missouri plains.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1874, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1858, \"end\": 1866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_Tigers\", \"score\": 0.9963771670512117, \"rank\": 0.0027049876419749613, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_Tigers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_Tigers\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Carvajal\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1763}, {\"ngram\": \"a dramatic day\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"the sweltering heat\", \"from\": 1795, \"to\": 1814}, {\"ngram\": \"dusty course\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1831}, {\"ngram\": \"mayhem\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One water-stop was all that was available too.\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1921, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One water-stop\", \"from\": 1875, \"to\": 1889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Carvajal was motoring nicely when he spotted an orchard and fancied a mid-race snack.\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Carvajal\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"an orchard\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"a mid-race snack\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2007}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately for him, the apples were rotten and after suffering cramps he had to take a nap.\", \"from\": 2009, \"to\": 2103, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the apples\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"cramps\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"a nap\", \"from\": 2097, \"to\": 2102}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He still finished fourth.\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"First over the finish line was American Fred Lorz but just as he was about to be presented with the winning trophy by Alice Roosevelt, daughter of then US President Teddy, it was established that after suffering with cramp, he had hitched a ride for about half the race and jumped out a few kilometres from the finish line.\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2162, \"end\": 2170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999991889594787, \"rank\": 8.043964716831497e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2171, \"end\": 2180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Lorz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Lorz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Lorz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Frederick_Lorz\"}, {\"begin\": 2249, \"end\": 2264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Roosevelt_Longworth\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.7490100725312685e-21, \"text\": \"Alice Roosevelt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Roosevelt_Longworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alice_Roosevelt_Longworth\"}, {\"begin\": 2283, \"end\": 2295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US President\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/President_of_the_United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2296, \"end\": 2301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riley\", \"score\": 0.9995627055213996, \"rank\": 0.00041717605549211584, \"text\": \"Teddy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Teddy_Riley\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2157}, {\"ngram\": \"the winning trophy\", \"from\": 2227, \"to\": 2245}, {\"ngram\": \"daughter\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"cramp\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"a ride\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2376}, {\"ngram\": \"about half the race\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2400}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 2438, \"to\": 2453}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lorz insisted it was a practical joke and when his ban was eventually shortened, he would claim a form of redemption by winning the 1905 Boston marathon.\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2609, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2593, \"end\": 2599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 0.9999999970937097, \"rank\": 2.9059456652544444e-09, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Lorz\", \"from\": 2456, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"a practical joke\", \"from\": 2477, \"to\": 2493}, {\"ngram\": \"his ban\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2510}, {\"ngram\": \"a form\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2558}, {\"ngram\": \"redemption\", \"from\": 2562, \"to\": 2572}]}, {\"sentence\": \"American William Garcia had led for a while but he inhaled so much dust that he started coughing up blood and suffered a near-fatal stomach haemorrhage.\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2611, \"end\": 2619, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999991889594787, \"rank\": 8.043964716831497e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2620, \"end\": 2634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Garcia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"William Garcia\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Garcia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Garcia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"so much dust\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2682}, {\"ngram\": \"blood\", \"from\": 2711, \"to\": 2716}, {\"ngram\": \"a near-fatal stomach haemorrhage\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2762}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Len Taunyane, a member of the South African Tswana tribe present for the world fair attached to the Games, had been performing well before a pack of wild dogs forced him off the course and with extra length to cover, he had to be content with a ninth-placed finish.\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 3030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2765, \"end\": 2777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Len_Taunyane\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Len Taunyane\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Len_Taunyane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Len_Taunyane\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a member\", \"from\": 2779, \"to\": 2787}, {\"ngram\": \"the South African Tswana tribe\", \"from\": 2791, \"to\": 2821}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2843}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2870}, {\"ngram\": \"a pack\", \"from\": 2904, \"to\": 2910}, {\"ngram\": \"wild dogs\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 2923}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 2939, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"extra length\", \"from\": 2959, \"to\": 2971}, {\"ngram\": \"a ninth-placed finish\", \"from\": 3008, \"to\": 3029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA's Thomas Hicks - English born - eventually won with a time of 3:28.53, but he was essentially dragged home by his trainers towards the end as hallucinations took over.\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3203, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3094}, {\"ngram\": \"3:28.53\", \"from\": 3098, \"to\": 3105}, {\"ngram\": \"his trainers\", \"from\": 3146, \"to\": 3158}, {\"ngram\": \"the end\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3174}, {\"ngram\": \"hallucinations\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Those may be explained by the dose of strychnine - sometimes used as rodent poison - they gave him during the race along with some brandy and egg whites.\", \"from\": 3204, \"to\": 3357, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the dose\", \"from\": 3230, \"to\": 3238}, {\"ngram\": \"strychnine\", \"from\": 3242, \"to\": 3252}, {\"ngram\": \"rodent poison\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3286}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 3310, \"to\": 3318}, {\"ngram\": \"some brandy and egg whites\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps then, better that Daly kept to the steeplechase - the only time it was held at a 2590 metre distance.\", \"from\": 3359, \"to\": 3468, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daly\", \"from\": 3385, \"to\": 3389}, {\"ngram\": \"the steeplechase\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3414}, {\"ngram\": \"the only time\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3430}, {\"ngram\": \"a 2590 metre distance\", \"from\": 3446, \"to\": 3467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daly was the fancy of many, but American Jim Lightbody won gold in his first attempt at the event with the Irishman second in a time of 7:40.6.\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3613, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3502, \"end\": 3510, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999991889594787, \"rank\": 8.043964716831497e-06, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 3511, \"end\": 3524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Lightbody\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jim Lightbody\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Lightbody\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jim_Lightbody\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Daly\", \"from\": 3470, \"to\": 3474}, {\"ngram\": \"the fancy\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3488}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3533}, {\"ngram\": \"his first attempt\", \"from\": 3537, \"to\": 3554}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3567}, {\"ngram\": \"the Irishman\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3585}, {\"ngram\": \"a time\", \"from\": 3596, \"to\": 3602}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Galway native was a real all-rounder in his early athletics day, participating in the high jump and long jump while racing against the great Tom Hynes, the winner of the first professional marathon to be held in Ireland in 1909.\", \"from\": 3615, \"to\": 3847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3619, \"end\": 3625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/County_Galway\", \"sc