": 4301}, {\"ngram\": \"Corofin Rebels\", \"from\": 4306, \"to\": 4320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The issue of nationalism was rife at the meet in Greece with Daly, Con Leahy and Peter O'Connor initially being sent as Irish representatives before being claimed by Great Britain as only athletes nominated by national Olympic committees were eligible, something they reportedly did not find out until their arrival.\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4665, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4398, \"end\": 4404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9716201667393886, \"rank\": 0.02920865109349104, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 4416, \"end\": 4425, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Con_Leahy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Con Leahy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Con_Leahy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Con_Leahy\"}, {\"begin\": 4430, \"end\": 4444, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_O'Connor_(athlete)\", \"score\": 0.9999921764257577, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Peter O'Connor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_O'Connor_(athlete)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_O'Connor_(athlete)\"}, {\"begin\": 4469, \"end\": 4474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.7269795436886114, \"rank\": 0.37529272064333313, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 4515, \"end\": 4528, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999066988739078, \"rank\": 9.329121409150925e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The issue\", \"from\": 4349, \"to\": 4358}, {\"ngram\": \"nationalism\", \"from\": 4362, \"to\": 4373}, {\"ngram\": \"the meet\", \"from\": 4386, \"to\": 4394}, {\"ngram\": \"Daly\", \"from\": 4410, \"to\": 4414}, {\"ngram\": \"only athletes\", \"from\": 4532, \"to\": 4545}, {\"ngram\": \"national Olympic committees\", \"from\": 4559, \"to\": 4586}, {\"ngram\": \"their arrival\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"O'Connor had set a long jump world record in 1901, and it would hold as the Irish record until Carlos O'Connell went further some 89 years later in Maryland, America.\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4743, \"end\": 4748, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"score\": 0.7269795436886114, \"rank\": 0.37529272064333313, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irish_people\"}, {\"begin\": 4762, \"end\": 4778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_O'Connell\", \"score\": 0.9999861923436698, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos O'Connell\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_O'Connell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_O'Connell\"}, {\"begin\": 4815, \"end\": 4823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maryland\", \"score\": 0.9754373967877795, \"rank\": 0.016604726370623754, \"text\": \"Maryland\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maryland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Maryland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"O'Connor\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4675}, {\"ngram\": \"a long jump world record\", \"from\": 4684, \"to\": 4708}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 4825, \"to\": 4832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Myer Prinstein beat O'Connor to gold in Athens in 1906, but at the medal ceremony under the Union Jack, he unveiled an Irish flag in protest with Daly and Leahy helping to protect him.\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 5019, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4835, \"end\": 4849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myer_Prinstein\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Myer Prinstein\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myer_Prinstein\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Myer_Prinstein\"}, {\"begin\": 4875, \"end\": 4881, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999903352826106, \"rank\": 9.664810836289676e-06, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2004_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4954, \"end\": 4964, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irish flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 4990, \"end\": 4995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Leahy\", \"score\": 0.9999999994479367, \"rank\": 5.522443579619818e-10, \"text\": \"Leahy\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Leahy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Patrick_Leahy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"O'Connor\", \"from\": 4855, \"to\": 4863}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 4867, \"to\": 4871}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal ceremony\", \"from\": 4898, \"to\": 4916}, {\"ngram\": \"the Union Jack\", \"from\": 4923, \"to\": 4937}, {\"ngram\": \"protest\", \"from\": 4968, \"to\": 4975}, {\"ngram\": \"Daly\", \"from\": 4981, \"to\": 4985}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PETER O'CONNOR: THE IRISH ANTELOPE \\\"I do not know exactly what made me do it, but it was just a feeling I had,\\\" Daly told the Connacht Tribune of their protest in 1958.\", \"from\": 5021, \"to\": 5190, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5021, \"end\": 5035, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_O'Connor_(athlete)\", \"score\": 0.9999921764257577, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"PETER O'CONNOR\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_O'Connor_(athlete)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_O'Connor_(athlete)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"THE IRISH ANTELOPE\", \"from\": 5037, \"to\": 5055}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 5071, \"to\": 5083}, {\"ngram\": \"just a feeling\", \"from\": 5110, \"to\": 5124}, {\"ngram\": \"Daly\", \"from\": 5133, \"to\": 5137}, {\"ngram\": \"the Connacht Tribune\", \"from\": 5143, \"to\": 5163}, {\"ngram\": \"their protest\", \"from\": 5167, \"to\": 5180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daly was selected to compete in the 1908 Olympics in London but injury ruled that out before he relocated to America where he continued to run for a number of years - finishing second in the 1909 Yonkers marathon, the second oldest in the USA after the Boston event.\", \"from\": 5192, \"to\": 5458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5245, \"end\": 5251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9984907675771274, \"rank\": 0.0015115135631261012, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 5388, \"end\": 5404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonkers_Marathon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yonkers marathon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonkers_Marathon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yonkers_Marathon\"}, {\"begin\": 5431, \"end\": 5434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999999735896384, \"rank\": 2.6182333198188848e-08, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://